<deployment_wisdom>
⚠️ DEPLOYMENT INTELLIGENCE - NOT DEPLOYMENT STUPIDITY ⚠️

INTELLIGENT PATTERNS:
1. Sync scripts ONLY sync files - NO git operations
2. NEVER use rsync --delete (can wipe directories)
3. Use excludes, don't delete files to "clean up"  
4. Check references before excluding files
5. Prefer justfile/Makefile over random shell scripts
6. Scripts should be idempotent and predictable

MATHEMATICAL PRINCIPLE: Deployment reliability ∝ simplicity²
Complex deployment scripts = exponential failure probability

GOLDEN RULE: Scripts move files. That's it. No commits, no cleanup, no magic.
</deployment_wisdom>

